(5005,E'1033 N Jackson St',E'Luverne',E'MN',56156,NULL,NULL,E'First Baptist Church',E'Whitwam, Ward B.',E'c.1960s',E'One of 4 churches in Luverne designed by the Sioux Falls-based architect (American Reformed Church, United Methodist Church, First Baptist Church, St. Catherine\'s Catholic Church), a unique situation for a small town, and Whitwam tried to make all 4 distinct from each other; this church originally had a large gabled church flanked on the ends with single-story segments that featured interesting, sculptural concrete roof that have since been replaced with gables that reduce the entire design (at least on the exterior) to the mundane.'),
