(5008,E'1401 100th St E',E'Bloomington',E'MN ',55425,NULL,NULL,E'Martin Luther Manor',E'Fasth, Hillstrom & Horty',E'1960-61',E'1962 AIA Minnesota Honor Award; 78-acres of land purchased by 17 Lutheran Churches in Minneapolis; 62-acres sold to the City of Bloomington and the school district to help raise capital for the building. Construction began in 1960, completed in 1961, originally with 96 beds. Major additions in 1984 (north building and Highland Manor); Meadow Woods Assisted Living added to campus in 1989; renamed Martin Luther Care Center in 2008 ahead of 2009-10 renovation. '),
(5009,E'13005 Sunset Trail',E'Plymouth',E'MN',55441,NULL,NULL,E'Sunset Hills School',E'Patch & Erickson',E'1963',E'Academic building designed on a 30ft x 30ft module overall, with the exception of two cooridors on a 10-ft grid; steel frame design to allow for high adaptability and a quick, 5-month building period with low price per sq ft ($10.74 at the time of const.).; Success of design led to design of Greenwood School in 1965; Builder: Adolfson & Peterson, Inc.; Structural Engineer: K.M. Clark Engineering Co.'),
