(5017,E'12 Skillman Ln',E'North Oaks',E'MN',55127,NULL,NULL,E'Dr. & Mrs Roger Ewert Residence',E'Stageberg, James',E'1960',E'Spacious one-room house built for a childless couple; the principal method of defining areas for sleeping (2), kitchen, dining, garden living, and fireplace were by varying the levels on the floor. Named one of the 20-best architect-designed houses by Architectural Record magazine in 1962. Mrs. Ewert noted "It\'s a very odd house. Most people wouldn\'t want it. It\'s strictly for us, and we love it." An addition was added to the back of the house sometime between 1974-85, based on Ramsey County aerial imagery.'),
