(5074,E'18360 Minnetonka Blvd',E'Deephaven',E'MN',55391,NULL,NULL,E'Grace Lutheran Church (add\'n)',E'Armstrong, Schlichting, Torseth & Skold',E'1966',E'Large addition dwarfing the original 1951, traditional brick colonial church; the congregation (organized in 1946 by the Northwest Synod of the United Lutheran Church in America) built the initial, $60,000 section with a long-range program to eventually replace it with a larger edifice as a main church and convert the original into a parish house. The first addition (1954), a $65,000 education wing extending from the west of the original church, was designed with two large halls that could be divided into 7 classrooms (at the time there were 300 students); the 1954 add\'n was designed by McEnary & Krafft (Builder: Otten Const. Co.). The 1966 addition connects to the end of the 1954 wing. The 1966 addition includes a new nave that seats 400; 16 classrooms, office, library, and choir space.'),
