(5079,E'1575 Charlton St',E'West St Paul',E'MN',55118,NULL,NULL,E'St Stephen\'s Lutheran Church',E'Armstrong, Schlichting, Torseth & Skold',E'c.1963',E'The original structure, a slightly bent gabled wing running from SW to NE, was completed by 1964 at a cost of approx. $500,000; the next portion, a $503,000 hexagonal sanctuary (tall with stained glass clerestory windows shaded by long overhangs), was completed in 1969. A later section was added to the NW, giving the building an aerial appearance of being some kind of bird or spaceship.'),
(5080,E'7687 Long Lake Rd',E'Mounds View',E'MN',55112,NULL,NULL,E'Sunrise Methodist Church',E'Johnson, Roger T.',E'1965-66',E'A transformative addition to a 1956 structure received an AIA MN Honor Award (1967), judges said "The building is a strong and simple statement on a rather hostile site" and "There is great economy in architectural expression with a degree of primitiveness." Alas there have been some poorly planned additions that mar much of the award-winning design, leaving only the larger sanctuary mostly untouched.'),
