(5115,E'700 Whispering Lane',E'Winona',E'MN',55987,NULL,NULL,E'Father Damian Hall (St Mary\'s)',E'Flad-Smith & Assoc.',E'1961-62',E'Replacing a smaller building of the same name on the site of the old college farm; Father Damian Hall was for Residence for Sacred Heart seminarians; later converted into a standard residence hall for St. Mary\'s and renamed Watters Hall. The building was designed to have two wings built off a central chapel in separate phases, but only the first wing (1961-62) and chapel (1966-67) were built. Named after Father Damien of Molokai (later canonized as Saint Damien)'),
(5116,E'700 Terrace Heights',E'Winona',E'MN',55987,NULL,NULL,E'Skemp Hall (St Mary\'s)',E'Unknown',E'1965-66',E'Originally built as a two-level gymnasium annex to Heffron Hall, it was remodeled in the 1960s into a three-story residence hall at a cost of $392,000; Thomas A. Skemp was athletic director for the school from 1919-32.'),
(5117,E'15817 Woodgate Rd S',E'Minnetonka',E'MN',55345,NULL,NULL,E'Showcase of Homes #35 (1960)',E'Hugh B. Thorson, Builder',E'1960',E'Contemporary flat-roof, 3-bedroom walk-out built as part of "Thorson\'s Woodgate Addition," consisting of 60 wooded lots. Builder: Hugh B. Thorson; built in time for the May 1960 Showcase of Homes. Thorson had a track record of building homes for notable mid-century architects, this may have been a variant of a plan house, though Thorson\'s own advertising for the development calls him “designer” and builder.'),
