(5126,E'5760 E River Rd',E'Fridley',E'MN',55432,NULL,NULL,E'Georgetown Courts Apartments (Phase II)',E'Cooperman, James M.',E'1969',E'The 27-acre, master-planned site developed by Maurice M. Filister (Filister Enterprises) with Cooperman and designer Paul Albitz; the idea came to Filister from the real Georgetown (DC) and bcame a multi-phase, $5-6M project with 11 apartment buildings supported by a recreational building, enclosed parking, pools, park space; the apartments were intended to look like a row of townhouses with different brick, paint, trim, and rooflines; Name later tweaked to Georgetown On the River Apartments.'),
