(5128,E'16023 Minnetonka Blvd',E'Minnetonka',E'MN',55345,NULL,NULL,E'Minnetonka Lutheran Church',E'Hustad, Donald',E'1961-62',E'Original permit missing; first section of building under construction in 1953; From 1959-60 it was the temporary home of the brand new Country Day School which would later become the Highcroft Country Day School and in turn merged into The Blake School. The church\'s first leader, Rev. Axel Anderson, died in a car crash in 1960; the "new" main sanctuary built from 1961-62 by T.M. Carlson & Son; ‘95 addn designed by by ATS&R; 2019: Bethlehem Lutheran Church Twin Cities – Minnetonka.'),
