(5147,E'4624 Mounthall Terrace',E'Minnetonka',E'MN',55345,NULL,NULL,E'Merlin & Donna Krupp Residence',E'Unknown',E'1962',E'Split-level contemporary built for Merlin Krupp, an illustrator in the advertising field; Wallace T. Bruce, owner of the builder Bruce Construction Co., attended the U of Minnesota in the 1930s and studied architecture but did not graduate; the entrance has a series of dramatic vertical windows. '),
(5148,E'15702 Woodgate Rd S',E'Minnetonka',E'MN',55345,NULL,NULL,E'Darryl L. Ulrich Residence',E'Stageberg, James',E'1964',E'Part of what was originally Thorsen\'s Woodgate developemement; this house is a striking modern work built on the edge of a steep hill: the main house is two rectangular forms connected by a central spine; the main door crosses a bridge from the street to the end of the spine; the flat roofs are accented by bold forms, the garage tucks into the side of the house. The original owner was an engineer.'),
(5149,E'410 Colvill St W',E'Cannon Falls',E'MN',55009,NULL,NULL,E'St Pius V Church',E'Eugene V. Schaefer & Assoc.',E'1964-65',E'The use of terrazzo flooring, particularly around the altar, was featured in an ad for The Northwest Terrazzo Association in the January-February 1966 issue of Northwest Architect. Congregation formed in 1856; this is the 3rd church, built on the site of the 2nd church which was demolished in 1964. Addition in 1985 added extra classrooms, a new kitchen, and offices; 2013 addition on south side.'),
