(5151,E'104 E Henderson St',E'Hendricks',E'MN',56136,NULL,NULL,E'Christ Lutheran Church',E'Gjelten & Schellberg',E'c.1963',E'Wisconsin potter Karl Christiansen was commissioned to make baptismal fonts and candle holders.'),
(5152,E'15630 E 4th St ',E'Ettrick',E'WI',54627,NULL,NULL,E'Living Hope Lutheran Church (educational bldg)',E'Gjelten & Schellberg',E'1964',E'Firm originally based in Forest City, Rochester office established in 1966; One of the works of Gordon O. Gjelten, who would go on to lead the firm\'s Rochester office in 1966; Sleek, one-story educational wing (Pastoral Center) with a floating accordion roof, original proposed cost of $68K; alas, at some point someone made the questionable decision to put a hip roof on top of the accordion roof; the interior photos show the accordion roof is still there but the clerestory windows are now obscured by the hip roof.'),
