(5224,E'1001 Highway 25 NW',E'Watertown',E'MN',55388,NULL,NULL,E'Watertown High School',E'Patch & Erickson',E'c.1960s',E'Many additions, later renamed Watertown-Mayer High School.'),
(5225,E'274 Labeaux Ave NE',E'Hanover',E'MN',55341,NULL,NULL,E'Hanover Elementary School',E'Patch & Erickson',E'c.1960s',NULL),
(5226,E'309 Jefferson Ave SW',E'Watertown',E'MN',55388,NULL,NULL,E'Watertown Clinic',E'Patch & Erickson',E'c.1960s',NULL),
(5227,E'4572 County Road 61',E'Moose Lake',E'MN',55767,NULL,NULL,E'Mercy Hospital',E'Patch & Erickson',E'1963',E'Originally opened as a 20-bed hospital; 25-bed nursing home addition opened in 1964; more additions in 1968, 1977, 1993, 2001, and 2015'),
(5228,E'301 Highway 65 S',E'Mora',E'MN',55051,NULL,NULL,E'Kanabec County Hospital (add\'n)',E'Patch & Erickson',E'1961',E'Addition to the original 1945 building (with prior \'53 add\'n); the \'61 project added an obstetrics suite, new operating room, new lab and x-ray department and cost $88,000; substantial subsequent additions in the 1970s, 1997, and 2015.'),
(5229,E'1310 Wayzata Blvd W',E'Long Lake',E'MN',55356,NULL,NULL,E'Hanson House',E'Patch & Erickson',E'1960',E'Popular fine dining restaurant designed to take in the view of Long Lake; later known as Billy\'s Lighthouse (the owner was named Bill Light, closed in 2006) and in 2015 reopened as Birch\'s on the Lake Brewhouse & Supperclub. '),
(5230,E'2015 3rd Ave',E'Anoka',E'MN',55303,NULL,NULL,E'First National Bank of Anoka',E'Unknown',E'1964',E'Substantial drive-through addition to the south-side with offices on top.'),
(5231,E'27500 Kirby Ave',E'Chisago City',E'MN',55013,NULL,NULL,E'Camp Ojiketa Chapel',E'Patch & Erickson',E'c.1960s',E'Interesting, rustic chapel designed for a Lutheran camp for girls (and later boys) on Green Lake; the . After the camp closed in 2006, it was turned into Ojiketa Regional Park in 2008 thanks to the work of The Trust for Public Land, State of Minnesota, Chisago City, and donations. The Chapel is now a rentable venue (e.g. weddings) known as Ojiketa\'s Birchwood Chapel.'),
(5232,E'601 Red River Ave S',E'Cold Spring',E'MN',56320,NULL,NULL,E'Gloria Dei Lutheran Church',E'Patch & Erickson',E'1964-65',E'The sanctuary features a delicate A-frame that flares out slightly as it descends; the east end has a large number stained glass windows on a vertical wood wall; the base is stone; there is a matching office/event room with a simple low-pitch roof.'),
(5233,E'1425 Madison Ave',E'Detroit Lakes',E'MN',56501,NULL,NULL,E'Lamplighter Manor',E'Patch & Erickson',E'c.1960s',E'Renamed Ecumen - Lamplighter Manor.'),
(5234,E'5100 Eden Ave',E'Edina',E'MN',55436,NULL,NULL,E'Edin 100 Office Building',E'Patch & Erickson',E'1968',E'Three-story office building on stilts above a parking area.'),
(5235,E'6315 University Ave NE',E'Fridley',E'MN',55432,NULL,NULL,E'Fridley State Bank',E'Patch & Erickson',E'1963',E'Through various mergers it ended up as a Wells Fargo Bank branch.'),
(5236,E'910 Ash St',E'Alexandria',E'MN',56308,NULL,NULL,E'Bethel Manor',E'Patch & Erickson',E'c.1960s',E'Renamed Ecumen Bethel Manor & Winona Shores of Alexandria.'),
(5237,E'75 Main St N',E'Kimball',E'MN',55353,NULL,NULL,E'State Bank of Kimball',E'Patch & Erickson',E'c.1960s',E'Later merged and renamed Harvest Bank.'),
(5238,E'200 Cavanaugh Dr',E'Shakopee ',E'MN',55379,NULL,NULL,E'Rubber Industries, Inc.',E'Patch & Erickson',E'c.1960s',E'The compound has had additions.'),
(5239,E'150 Wayzata Blvd E',E'Wayzata',E'MN',55391,NULL,NULL,E'Highland Apartments',E'Patch & Erickson',E'1960',E'3 two-story buildings. '),
(5240,E'16625 Excelsior Blvd',E'Minnetonka',E'MN',55345,NULL,NULL,E'Glen Lake Baptist Church',E'Patch & Erickson',E'1967-68',E'Congregation began using the location in 1961 before building the new 200-seat chapel with 14 classrooms, nursery and office; Builder: Thomas S. Silvis Const. Co.; Later sold, became Slavic Baptist Church of Transfiguration.'),
(5241,E'3351 Independence Ave N',E'New Hope',E'MN',55428,NULL,NULL,E'Beautiful Savior Lutheran Church',E'Patch & Erickson',E'1963-64',E'Building designed to be a horizontal form visible from the main road (when built): Originally located on County Road 18, the road was turned into U.S. Highway 169, removing the primary access to the building, also the freeway wall further obscured the view of the church; Coincidentally, Beautiful Savior moved to this location after it\'s previously location was also affected by highway construction; The sanctuary designed to seat 300 with a Sunday School for 170 children (there were subsequent expansions to the north side); Builder: Droher Const. Co.; the congregation moved in the 1990s; has been a few other congregations since.'),
(5242,E'5405 Mount Normandale Curve',E'Bloomington',E'MN',55437,NULL,NULL,E'Frank D. Werner Residence',E'Unknown',E'1962',E'Commanding, private position at the top of a hill, out of sight from the culdesac; the 3 acre site grandfathered in the right to have horses (as noted in the 2008 real estate listing); Frank D. Werner grew up on a farm but preferred engineering (earning a PhD in aerospace engineering from Johns Hopkins), founding Rosemount Engineering in 1956; after it\'s tremendous success in aerospace engineering (including the space program) plus his interest in skiing led to the pioneering, all-plastic Rosemount Ski Boots, he moved to Jackson Hole in 1970 to focus on R&D work.'),
(5243,E'6800 Willow Lane N',E'Brooklyn Center',E'MN',55430,NULL,NULL,E'Ray Perry Residence',E'Polivka, John',E'1965',E'Subject of its own feature in the Minneapolis Tribune (December 6, 1970); The owners stated "Ordinary rectangular rooms are dull. We asked our architect to put all the different levels and angles he could into our house." Thankfully, Polivka kept it from going out of control, instead designing a tasteful, bent rambler taking full advantage of its lot sloping down to the Mississippi River, opening to the private view (facing an island, and working on preserving the existing trees); exterior is etched cedar and feather rock, with redwood used on trim and for the roofed deck facing the river; originally had an attached carport, but it\'s been converted into a garage; the low-pitched roof overhands the front of the house to form a covered walkway to the main door; ; the interior uses the same feather-rock for fireplaces in the living room and downstairs playroom, and the back of the fireplaces make a rock wall for the foyer, with an open stairway curving around it so both levels can be seen from the entrance (a feature boasted about in a 1988 listing for the house); the playroom had a carpeted conversation pit; the original interior design was as wild as the client\'s original instructions to the architects, with bold colors everywhere, natural shake walls for the den, and general decor.; Perry was an executive at Bemis Co.'),
(5244,E'323 10th Ave SE',E'Minneapolis',E'MN',55414,NULL,NULL,E'Alpha Phi Sorority (add\'n)',E'Griswold & Rauma',E'1966',E'Addition to rear of 1912 sorority house;  From the "Griswold, Rauma, Egge & Olson Architectural Commissions Records" at the Hennepin History Museum.'),
(5245,E'2200 Pascal St',E'Roseville',E'MN',55113,NULL,NULL,E'Rose Mall apartment complex',E'Van Housen, Thomas C.',E'1964-68',E'The $2M complex consists of 9 Y-shaped (all sides equal length) buildings, each holding 18-units each (162 total); the 9 buildings are arranged so they connect into 3 groups of 2-, 3-, and 4-buildings in order to form court years in between; 243-car parking lot, tennis courts, and swimming pool; Owner/Builder: Zimmerman Realty Co.'),
(5246,E'250 Hwy 19 Blvd',E'Red Wing',E'MN',55066,NULL,NULL,E'Central Research Laboratories',E'Griswold & Rauma',E'1962',E'Single-story office and manufacturing plant structure with the flat roof forming an overhang around the perimeter with large exterior concrete posts. The faces were designed with a combination of window walls and patterned block for the manufacturing and shop lavatory areas, breaking up what could\'ve easily been a monotonous facade. The office end of the structure forms a slight U-shape, fronted with aggregate and some limited plantings. The roof is higher over the manufacturing floor, though this is set back due to the overhangs that wrap the building. Add\'n by Griswold & Rauma in \'66; the company specializes in hazardous material handling products (perhaps explaining why the structure is built far from the adjacent highway and street; Company moved to larger quarters, the structure is became city-owned property overseen by the Red Wing Port Authority.'),
(5247,E'3901 University Ave NE',E'Columbia Heights',E'MN',55421,NULL,NULL,E'Minneapolis Electric Steel Castings Company Offices',E'Griswold & Rauma',E'1969',E'Manufacturer of castings for construction and mining equipment.'),
(5248,E'400 Main St E',E'New Prague',E'MN',56071,NULL,NULL,E'New Prague Public Library',E'David J. Griswold & Assoc.',E'1963',E'The local branch was first started in 1960, part of the Scott County Library System (though it\'s technically right across the border in Le Sueur County); 2008 addition to the back (Mary J. Tikalsky Reading Room).'),
(5249,E'901 Luther Place',E'Albert Lea',E'MN',56007,NULL,NULL,E'St. John\'s Lutheran Home',E'Gjelten & Schellberg',E'1965',E'Firm\'s office based in Forest City, Iowa (it later had a Rochester office); the building is included as a featured work in Willis E. Schellberg\'s 1970 AIA directory entry. Large nursing home; several newer additions.'),
(5250,E'808 W Front St',E'Albert Lea',E'MN',56007,NULL,NULL,E'Albert Lea Tribune',E'Unknown',E'1960',E'Builder: Sorenson Construction Co.'),
(5251,E'211 W Richway Dr',E'Albert Lea',E'MN',56007,NULL,NULL,E'Brookside School',E'Unknown',E'c.1966',E'Two-story school with circular floorplan; Closed in the 21st century and converted into the Brookside Education Center.'),
