(5269,E'4241 Kings Dr',E'Minnetonka',E'MN ',55345,NULL,NULL,E'House',E'Ekberg-Petri Architects',E'1960',E'Two-story colonial named "Best Home for the Money" in Minnesota by American Home Magazine in October 1960. Part of builder/developer Robert Mason\'s Royal Hills development in Minnetonka; Mason (who was in his 20s when it began) built many different styles of homes in the development: ramblers, split levels, two story colonials and a few contemporaries.  Price range was in the mid-$20ks to mid-$30ks.  Mason was in his mid 20s when he started building homes in the development.'),
