(5282,E'4000 28th St S',E'Moorhead',E'MN',56560,NULL,NULL,E'Lutheran Church of the Good Shepherd',E'Sovik, Mathre & Madson',E'1967',E'Received AIA MN Honor Award (1968), the jury noted "The building has much of the visual quality of high Romanesque. Fine Interior space, sensitively used materials. Skillful detailing and use of materials really outstanding." It received an award for architectural merit at the 29th annual National Conference on Religious Architecture. Designed to seat 500 and provide spaces primarily for church staff. By 2020 the building appears to have suffered through some clumsy additions that have neutered the exterior somewhat.'),
(5283,E'8243 Demontreville Trail N',E'Lake Elmo',E'MN',55042,NULL,NULL,E'Jesuit Retreat House',E'Cerny Associates',E'1967',E'Received AIA MN Honor Award (1968), the jury noted its "Human scale, warm and serene quality. Obviously pleasant place to be." Designed to provide a chapel, lounge, and dining facilities for 60 retreatants and staff lodging for three priests. Part of larger Demontreville Jesuit Retreat House complex off Lake De Montreville. Address was originally listed as “3900 Demontreville Road, North St. Paul” (before the incorporation of Lake Elmo).'),
(5284,E'14980 Diamond Path W',E'Rosemount',E'MN',55068,NULL,NULL,E'Lutheran Church of Our Savior',E'Progressive Design Associates',E'1967',E'Received AIA MN Honor Award (1968), the jury noted "Building has fine sculptural qualities but made no concession in their development and thus is free of extraneous cliches." The exterior of the sanctuary is an interesting trapezoidal form clad in wood shingles. Suffered an incongruous addition to the south of the building.'),
(5285,E'2335 W Goodrich Ave',E'St Paul',E'MN',55105,NULL,NULL,E'Saint Paul Seminary',E'Bettenburg, Townsend, Stolte & Comb',E'1966',E'Received AIA MN Honor Award (1968), the jury noted the "[c]haracter of the buildings has warm, human scale." The scale quickly got crowded when the Saint John Vianney College Seminary campus on Lake Johanna shut down in 1971 due to decline enrollment (sold to what is now University of Northwestern); that undergraduate program moved to share space with the Saint Paul Seminary graduate school and was later merged into The Seminaries of Saint Paul. New buildings were built in the 1980s just north of this one. Later renamed Brady Hall, then the Brady Education Center. [Address is approximate]'),
(5286,E'1673 Westwood Hills Dr',E'St Louis Park',E'MN ',55426,NULL,NULL,E'Parade Home No. 18 (1961)',E'Gerrish, Harry E.',E'1961',E'The Parade of Homes guide boasted: "From the Versailles collection collection comes this original design by architect Harry Eldon Gerrish. Situationed on a spacious lot overlooking Westwood Hills Golf Course, the homes exterior is highlighted by a private garden court and fountain. A dramatic sense of space is achieved in the living and dining room with a double high beamed ceiling and free standing wall partitions." Based on images from a 2015 listing, much of the design remains intact. Builder: McNulty Construction Co.'),
(5287,E'250 Craigbrook Way NE',E'Fridley',E'MN',55432,NULL,NULL,E'1961 Better Homes & Gardens Idea Home',E'Schmidt & Stuart (Lubbock, TX)',E'1961',E'Parade Home No. 40 (1961), this Idea Home was featured in the Sept. 1961 issue and featured “Hydronic heating”, den with "monkey pod" paneling and vinyl cork tiled floor, glass window to wooded site, and a Medallion home status. Builder: Pearson Bros., part of their Craigway Estates development. It appears to be a climate-adapted, mirrored version of the Five Star Home Model 3109-D, in particular.'),
