(5293,E'522 Minnesota Ave NW',E'Bemidji',E'MN',56601,NULL,NULL,E'U.S. Post Office',E'Unknown',E'1960',E'Transferred to the U.S. General Services Administration (GSA) in 1974 and converted into the Federal Building; made of concrete brick and polished granite, the building features concrete columns framing a flat roof and a terrazzo lobby inside. The building has four floors, a basement, and a mezzanine. Most recently housed offices of the Bureau of Indian Affairs and the Indian Health Service. In 2018, though, the federal government announced its intent to have those agencies relocate and vacate the structure. GSA offered the building up for sale in 2020.'),
