(5299,E'400 15th Ave SW',E'Austin',E'MN',55912,NULL,NULL,E'St. Mark\'s Lutheran Retirement Home',E'Patch & Erickson',E'1962-63',E'Planning began in 1958, with 10-acres purchased that year, as 21 local Evangelical Lutheran Church congregations began planning together for a retirement home to service the Austin Circuit (spread across Mower and parts of Dodge, Freeborn, and Fillmore counties); the original plan was to begin with a 60-bed, T-shape development that could be expanded as needed; Donald Erickson represented the firm at the announcement; at the time of ground-breaking, it was set to be 72-bed, 3 unit with a budget of $700k.'),
