(5303,E'1118 Main St N',E'Austin',E'MN',55912,NULL,NULL,E'Downtown Plaza',E'Thorsen & Thorshov',E'1963-64',E'The first indoor shopping mall in MN outside of the Twin Cities; developed on 16-acres of what had been considered marginal marshland that was subject to flooding; 136,000 cubic yards of fill was used to raise the ground 5-6 feet, mostly dredged from the adjacent Red Cedar River; The structure was two buildings, separated by mall, under one roof enclosing a total of 105,000 square feet and using 35,000 concrete blocks; the opening anchors included a Tempo department store (self-service subsidiary of Gamble\'s) and a Red Owl Family Center (combo of Red Owl Food Stores and Snyder\'s Drug Stores); Builder: Kraus-Anderson, which employed local Wagner Const. Co.; later closed and converted into a food manufacturing plant.'),
