(5312,E'1414 College Way',E'Fergus Falls',E'MN',56537,NULL,NULL,E'Fergus Falls State Junior College',E'Bettenburg, Townsend, Stolte & Comb',E'1967-68',E'Original bid for the first 3 buildings of a campus site-plan that included 7 structures arranged around a C-shaped pathway on an expansive 148-acre campus site; the architectural highlight in the original design is a covered mall on the east side of the original plan, between what were initially designated Building A (Commons and Administration) and Building B (Science); the top of the promenade is still visible even as the spaces between buildings were filled with new structures connecting them all; Campus reorganized in 2003 and became Minnesota State Community and Technical College (M State) Fergus Falls.'),
(5313,E'100 Southern Ave E',E'Underwood',E'MN',56586,NULL,NULL,E'Underwood School (add\'n)',E'Unknown',E'1967-68',E'Substantial, $303,000 addition including 6 elementary class rooms, new gymnasium seating 700, shower and locker rooms, bathrooms, and administrative office areas along with remodling the old school and gym.; Builder: Edlund Const. Co. (Valley City, ND).'),
(5314,E'411 S Otter Ave',E'Parkers Prairie',E'MN',56361,NULL,NULL,E'Parkers Prairie High School (add\'n)',E'Matson & Wegleitner ',E'1967-68',E'Substantial, $675,000 addition on west side of original school buildings, adding 8 classrooms, a library, offices, and new gym; Hasslen Const. (Ortonville).'),
