(5358,E'1100 Minnesota Ave W',E'Walker',E'MN',56484,NULL,NULL,E'Community Church of Walker',E'Unknown',E'1963-64',E'Rustic modern A-frame; Land purchased in December 1962; it has been a part of the United Church of Christ since its construction.'),
(5359,E'161 School Ave',E'Watkins',E'MN',55389,NULL,NULL,E'Watkins School',E'Unknown',E'1960',E'The $216,000 structure dealt with not only financial, but religious dissensions; the original site was rejected by the state dept. of education; the budget was $184k, and an additional bond issue of $32k took two special elections to pass; the structure was designed to house 4 classrooms, library, gym, hot lunch cafeteria, and administrative offices; the fight over funding was between Catholic and non-Catholic interests (at the time, the town only had 3 non-Catholic families).'),
