 in small post offices that were a-contextual and stylistically homogeneous (emphasizing economy over creativity). There was notably no emphasis on landscaping. The topic is explored in the "USPS Nationwide Historic Context Study: Postal Facilities Constructed or Occupied Between 1940 and 1971" (URS Group, Inc. prepared for U.S. Postal Service, September 2012.).'),
