(5545,E'23852 240th Ct',E'Winsted',E'MN',55395,NULL,NULL,E'House',E'Bloomberg, Herbert',E'1968',E'Bloomberg was a developer in Edina and Chanhassen who dabbled in design (best known for his Chanhassen Dinner Theater); his one-off clients tended to be affluent people, and the houses he designed them often had many commonalities, many of which are present here: expensive finishes, avoiding traditional square/rectangular rooms, an indoor pool; the house was originally on 50+ acres which have since been shaved off to reduce it to a still-large 3.6acres on "The Point."'),
