(5567,E'862 Homestead Village Ln SE',E'Rochester',E'MN',55904,NULL,NULL,E'Homestead Village',E'Ellerbe & Co.',E'1960-61',E'After the construction of over 100 single-family homes on the Mayo Homestead addition just north of here, Mayo Properties realized it needed more housing and had Ellerbe design a 102-unit apartment village as Mayo Fellows housing on an unused portion of the original homestead; units are either 2 or 3 bedroom, and widely separate by park-like grounds in a zigzag arrangement (2 units per building, 51 buildings); 1969 addition added separate structures for carports and storage units for each apartment; built on a farm bought by Dr. W.W. Mayo in 1875 and previously known as the Mayo Homestead.'),
