(5622,E'4700 Miller Ave',E'White Bear Lake',E'MN',55110,NULL,NULL,E'White Bear Lake Municipal Building',E'Ellerbe & Co.',E'1961-62',E'The $400,000 structure designed to hold the fire department, police department, city council chambers, and other administrative options; the building was designed in two separate, single-story rectangular volumes, set in a L-shape arrangement and connected by an enclosed walkway; an 1990s addition enclosed it and broke-up the simplicity of the two volume design; the city maintained the previous city hall (originally at 803 2nd St), which later moved to an new, adjacent building to the east in 1988.'),
