(5774,E'1611 Park Ave',E'Minneapolis',E'MN',55404,NULL,NULL,E'Provident Mutual Life Insurance Co. building',E'Hammel & Green',E'1963-64',E'The insurance company described their new building as a "home on stilts." The 5,200sq structure was built on stilts to accomodate ground-level parking, with the front stairwell enclosed by white stucco; the building originally only had a stairwell on the south side; estimated cost: $150,000. Builder: Bor-Son Const., Inc. By 2021 it housed the Legal Rights Center. '),
