(5841,E'28 Edgewater Ln',E'Sartell',E'MN',56377,NULL,NULL,E'House',E'Unknown',E'1962',E'Large ranch on the Mississippi River; described as being in the resurgent "Atomic Ranch" style during a 2021 sale. Exposed wood beams throughout, tongue & groove cedar ceilings, oak hardwood & cork flooring, custom louvered doors & 3 gas fireplaces.  In 2012 it was described as 4-bed/5-bath; in 2021 it was 5-bed (1 as study), 4 baths. Tasteful MCM in 2021. 2nd owners (c.1977) were Dr. David & Katherine Matthew; in 1997 the Mississippi River rose and came within 10 yards of the house.'),
(5842,E'904 7th St',E'Farmington',E'MN',55024,NULL,NULL,E'Math & Ann Fischer Residence',E'Unknown',E'1963',E'Interesting house that included the architect\'s original model in its first 2021 sale. The original design had a series of 3 connected forms loosely forming a large rectangular footprint: a main house with gable roof, a flat-roof garage, and in between an apparently glass-enclosed pool (gable-roof; it was possibly never glass-enclosed and just used as an especially elaborate pergola) with a flat-roof passage going along the side and connecting the garage to the house. The design is exceptionally sophisticated. By the 2021 sale the pool was removed, and the space was an open courtyard with the wood beams still in place. The main house features vaulted ceilings and a bold, statement fireplace with copper hood. The house has had updates but still appears to be aesthetically sound in 2021. Mathias H. "Math" Fischer (d. 2000) was head of the Fischer Sand & Aggregate Co. and later president of Apple Valley Ready Mix; Ann passed in 2021. '),
