(5858,E'2700 28th St E',E'Minneapolis',E'MN',55406,NULL,NULL,E'Aslesen Co.',E'Plagens-McGee Inc',E'1969-70',E'Office and warehouse; specifically credited to Robert McGee; Builder: Antler Corp. Aslesen Co. was a food and food-service-equipment firm originally founded in 1879 as a small grocery chain by Knud Aslesen. By 1970 it was the largest restaurant and institutional food service supplier in the Upper Midwest. The company saw even bigger growth with the rise in the popularity of frozen foods, electronic ranges, and faster cooking processes. It needed a new, expanded plant and was supported by the Minneapolis Industrial Development Commission (MIDC), a city-operated agency, to relocate to the Seward South urban renewal area and keep its tax base within the city. When it moved to the new facility in the summer of 1970 from its original home at 509 Washington Ave S., it required the change of what was the 7th-ever phone installed in Minneapolis by the Northwestern Bell Telephone Co. The company\'s work included design and installation of food-service equipment and distribution of institutional wholesale food supplies. The company was acquired by the Chicago-based Chicago Milwaukee Corp. in 1973, at the time it had annual sales of $17M. Major warehouse addition in 1975 (builder: Preston Haglin Co.).'),
