(5862,E'2519 25th St E',E'Minneapolis',E'MN',55406,NULL,NULL,E'Blesi-Evans Co.',E'Engineer: Melvin E. Evans',E'1965-66',E'Office and warehouse. Owner: Blesi-Evans Co.; Builder: Ron Jon Const. Co. (/s/ Ronald R. Johnson). The company\'s founder/manager, Melvin E. Evans (1924-2007), was a mechanical engineer (UMN grad) who designed the building himself. He earned a mechanical engineering degree from the University of Minnesota and successfully founded and managed the Blesi-Evans Company. The company consisted of mechanical engineers acting as manufacturer\'s agents in the generation, control, and utilization of steam, hot, and domestic water, serving industrial and manufacturing plants; it was acquired by Mulcahy Co. (an HVAC and plumbing company) in 2017.  '),
