(5963,E'4222 West Broadway',E'Robbinsdale',E'MN',55422,NULL,NULL,E'First Robbinsdale State Bank Drive-In Bank',E'Tudor, Thomas H.',E'1964',E'Heavily altered. The city\'s first drive-in banking facility; the $60,000 structure was linked to the main bank at 4180 West Broadway via pneumatic tubes to transmit official papers and correspondence. The red-brick structure initially had 2 drive-in teller windows and 2 walk-up windows. It featured a large, square canopy in a waffle-style roof. A specialist in bank design, Tudor had become the go-to architect for the First Bank System (which later became U.S. Bancorp), being appointed assistant manager of the building department of First Service Corp. (operations affiliate of parent First Bank Stock Corp.) in 1953 after already designing banks for the organization. The current banking facility looks very different. '),
