(5989,E'1814 2nd St NE',E'Minneapolis',E'MN',55418,NULL,NULL,E'Kuether Distribution Co.',E'Unknown',E'1963',E'The original section of this L-shaped building was the portion in the NW facing 112 19th Ave NE. Initial section (80x127x19\') permitted as a warehouse building; architect line left blank; owner/builder: William B. Kuether; 1966 add\'n (58.4x127x20) one-story warehouse designed by engineer G.T. Fitzgerald (Builder: Fitzgerald Bros.); 1976 add\'n (forming the "L" towards 2nd St NE) for Kuether Distribution Co. designed by engineer G.T. Fitzgerald (Builder: Fitzgerald Bros.); 1985-86 add\'n for new owner, a sheet metal firm (Builder: Earl Weikle & Sons).'),
(5990,E'1612 2nd St NE',E'Minneapolis',E'MN',55418,NULL,NULL,E'Sentryz Grocery',E'Draftsman: Carl Walter Swanberg',E'1962',E'Sentryz Grocery. A small portion of the current building may date to an 1953-54 addition (also by Walter & Frank Sentyrz) to an existing storefront that dated to the 1890s; however historical aerial photos show this structure barely matches the current footprint, built in 1962 as an addition for owner Walter Sentyrz (that initial footprint is a clean rectangle); Builder: Reco Const. Later additions gave it the current shape. As of 2021 it\'s still the Sentyrz Liquor & Supermarket. '),
